         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">Compared to <ref target="http://idp.bl.uk/database/oo_loader.a4d?pm=IOL Toch 830" type="external">IDP</ref>, recto and verso are to be reversed.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">: cf. Uv32.46d <hi>’sau māra bandhanāt</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">: cf. Uv32.47d <hi>nāstīdānīṃ punar bhavaḥ</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">: cf. Uv32.48b–53b <hi>marditā grāmakaṇṭakāḥ</hi>, i.e. actually Uv32.48b because of the number 48 in line a4.</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">: cf. Uv32.48a–53a <hi>uttīrṇo yena vai paṅkaḥ</hi>, i.e. actually Uv32.49a because of the preceding number 48.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">: At the end of the line, a little piece is flipped over from the verso.</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">: cf. Uv32.XX <hi>aśeṣaṃ bisapuṣpam iva</hi>.</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">: cf. Uv32.55e–81e <hi>apāraṃ hy urago jīrṇam iva</hi>.</note></p>
